BAC Secretariat to post all the required information in the GPPB Online Portal for the negotiated procurement under emergency cases, if warranted, and ensure to comply with the GPPB guidelines on the posting of required information related to procurement to the GPPB Online Portal;
BAC Secretariat to ensure that Omnibus Sworn Statement (OSS) provides the date it was executed and notarized, conform with the prescribed format and submitted within the prescribed period;
Requisitioning unit and BAC to ensure complete details on the Purchase Request (PR), Purchase Orders (PO) and other supporting documents and that all needed specifications of the requisitioned items are included therein that would be useful in determining the price reasonableness and compliance with specifications;
BAC Secretariat to ensure that the suppliers/bidders properly indicate the date of receipt as they sign the NOA and the NTP;
Municipal Accountant to review all supporting documents before processing of payment to ensure completeness thereof.

The Municipal Assessor to submit to the Municipal Treasurer the updated Real Property Tax Assessment Roll which will facilitate in the preparation of the Certified List of Taxpayers by the latter;

The Municipal Treasurer update the RPT Account Registers/Taxpayer’s index cards and submit the corresponding duly certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year to the Municipal Accountant as basis in the setting up of RPT/SET Receivables; and

The Municipal Accountant to make a detailed analysis of the Receivable accounts and their contra accounts to determine the cause/s of the discrepancies and effect the necessary adjustments in the books of accounts.

Management direct the:

The Municipal Accountant to:

Ensure an accurate recording of amounts in the Financial Statements as well as supporting schedules and see to it that totals of schedules match with balances presented in the notes to financial statements;

Provide schedules for Construction in Progress accounts within the general fund to have better understanding of the figures presented in the notes to financial statements;

Exhaust all possible options to retrieve documents in relation to Work/Zoo Animals account, and if this is not possible, consider the dropping of the account from the books; and

Prepare or update ledger cards for each class of PPE and reconcile it with balances in the general ledger of PPE accounts.

The Municipal Treasurer/Property Custodian to:

Prepare and submit the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE) on or before January 31 of each year;

Use the prescribed format of the RPCPPE and ensure accurate recording of the result of physical count in the RPCPPE and report must be properly filled up ensuring that all descriptions in the columns and items presented are reported and accounted for including the condition and whereabouts of the PPE;

Include all items of PPE in the conduct of physical count and incorporate all the results of the count in the RPCPPE; and

Prepare or update property cards for each category of PPE and reconcile it with the result of physical count of PPE through the RPCPPE.

The Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer/Property Custodian to:

Ensure the reconciliation of property and accounting records.

We recommended that the Municipal Government enhance its compliance with policies and procedures on Local Roads Asset Management System by:

Requiring the submission of the report of the Local Road Network by the GSO in order to implement and monitor the recognition of the account Local Road Network in the books of accounts;

Improving the maintenance of subsidiary ledger for the Road and it components;

Making proper disclosure in the Financial Statement of Road Network System;

Exercising proper reconciliation between Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network and Local Road Network Ledger Card and make the necessary adjustment; and

Providing cost to specific Road Network in order to have proper valuation and completeness of the Road Network Account.

We recommended that management direct the following:
Municipal Accountant
Ensure accurate recording of amounts in the Financial Statements as well as supporting schedules and see to it that totals of schedules match with balances presented in the notes to financial statements;
Provide schedules for Construction in Progress accounts within the general fund to have better understanding of the figures presented in the notes to financial statements;
