Prepare or update property cards for each category of PPE and reconcile it with the result of physical count of PPE through the RPCPPE.
Municipal Accountant and Municipal Treasurer/Property Custodian
Ensure the reconciliation of property and accounting records.

We recommended that management:
Develop strategies to identify projects, programs and activities that are workable and implementable within the year to get the maximum value of fund utilization considering the increasing prices of materials;
Fast-tract the implementation of all ongoing and unimplemented development projects programmed funded under the 20% DF to optimize utilization thereof and timely brings the desired benefits to its intended beneficiaries;
The MPDC and MEO regularly monitor the project status implementation by enhancing monitoring control that will facilitate timely corrective measure during the PPAs implementation cycle; and
Regularly update and reconcile their reports to avoid inconsistencies.

Recommendation:
We recommend that the Municipal Government enhance its compliance with policies and procedures on Local Roads Asset Management System by:
Requiring the submission of the report of the Local Road Network by the GSO in order to implement and monitor the recognition of the account Local Road Network in the books of accounts;
Improving the maintenance of subsidiary ledger for the Road and it components;
Making proper disclosure in the Financial Statement of Road Network System;
Exercising proper reconciliation between Report on the Physical Count of Local Road Network and Local Road Network Ledger Card and make the necessary adjustment; and
Providing cost to specific Road Network in order to have proper valuation and completeness of the Road Network Account.
Management Comment:
The Municipalilty explained that the conduct of inventory is currently on-going and is almost done. The report is now for consolidation and three (3) out of twenty-two (22) barangays were already consolidated. The Municipality further informed that they already provided the SL for the recognition of Road Network in the books of accounts and after the reports have been submitted  from the office of the Municipal Engineer, then necessary adjustment and disclosures shall be made. Moreover, Management promised to comply with the audit recommendations and ensure proper compliance with accounting and reporting guidelines under COA Circular No. 2015-008.

The GSO/MT and Accounting Unit will conduct reconciliation of their respective records in order to establish the existence, status/conditions and whereabouts of the assets;
Advise the inventory team to use property tags during the count to facilitate identification and location of the PPE;
The GSO/MT and Accountant shall have to maintain Property Cards and Equipment Ledger Cards, respectively, to ensure the accuracy and reliability of the property and accounting records;


Provide adequate information on the inventory reports such as the model, serial number, cost, conditions and property number to facilitate identification during the count;

Require clearance from retired/resigned officials and employees to clear them of their property accountability and cancel the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) for the returned items.

We recommend that the Local Chief Executive through the members of the Municipal Solid Waste Management Board (MSWMB) adopt the following courses of action:

Stop the operation of open dumpsite;
Procurement of recycling equipment to fully equip the MRF;
Strictly enforce the waste segregation policy at source; and
Establish a long-term storage facility for the residual wastes.

